1 …."
2 SECTION 1.(g) G.S. 160A-208.1 reads as rewritten:
3 "§ 160A-208.1. Disclosure of certain information prohibited.
4 (a) Disclosure Prohibited. – Notwithstanding Chapter 132 of the General Statutes or any
5 other law regarding access to public records, local tax records that contain information about a
6 taxpayer's income or receipts are not public records. A current or former officer, employee, or
7 agent of a city who in the course of service to or employment by the city has access to information
8 about the amount of a taxpayer's income or receipts may not disclose the information to any other
9 person unless the disclosure is made for one of the following purposes:
10 …
11 (4) To include on a property tax receipt the amount of property taxes due and the
12 amount of property taxes deferred on a residence classified under
13 G.S. 105-277.1B, the property tax homestead circuit breaker.
14 …."
15 SECTION 2. Notwithstanding G.S. 105-380 and G.S. 105-381, the governing body
16 of a taxing unit shall release the unpaid deferred taxes under G.S. 105-277.1B on any property
17 for which a disqualifying event has not occurred. Any lien under G.S. 105-355(a) corresponding
18 to the released deferred taxes is also extinguished.
19 SECTION 3. Section 1 of this act is effective for taxable years beginning on or after
20 July 1, 2026. The remainder of this act is effective July 1, 2026.
